8. Reference Implementation
Below is pseudo-code demonstrating the required logic for the core components.

8.1. Model Inference Engine (KV Cache Management)

```python
class DispatchAwareInferenceEngine:
    def generate(self, context, kv_cache=None):
        # 1. Load frozen KV cache if resuming (Prefix Caching)
        if kv_cache:
            self.attention_layers.load_kv(kv_cache)
            
        for token in self.decode_next_tokens(context):
            if self.parser.is_dispatch_wait_ack(token):
                # 2. Suspend: Freeze and serialize KV cache
                frozen_kv = self.attention_layers.freeze_kv()
                storage.save(context.dispatch_hash, frozen_kv)
                return SuspendSignal(hash=context.dispatch_hash)
                
            yield token

    def resume(self, dispatch_hash, resume_payload):
        # 3. Verify cryptographic signature
        if not crypto.verify(resume_payload.signature):
            raise SecurityViolationError()
            
        # 4. Restore KV cache and continue generation
        kv_cache = storage.load(dispatch_hash)
        new_context = append_to_context(resume_payload)
        return self.generate(new_context, kv_cache=kv_cache)
```


8.2. Orchestrator (State & Routing)

```python
class AgentOrchestrator:
    def dispatch_task(self, sub_agent, task):
        dispatch_hash = crypto.generate_signed_hash(task_id)
        context = build_context(task, dispatch_hash)
        
        # Trigger model generation
        result = inference_engine.generate(context)
        
        if isinstance(result, SuspendSignal):
            # Park the context, do not poll!
            self.state_db.park_context(result.hash, status="WAITING")
            return "Task suspended. Awaiting external event."

    def handle_external_event(self, task_id, result_data):
        dispatch_hash = self.state_db.get_hash(task_id)
        resume_payload = build_resume_payload(dispatch_hash, result_data)
        
        # Trigger model resumption
        inference_engine.resume(dispatch_hash, resume_payload)
        self.state_db.unpark_context(dispatch_hash)
```

9. Future Extensions

As agentic systems scale, the Dispatch-Wait Protocol will be extended to support:

Nested Dispatch (DAG Execution): Allowing a suspended sub-agent to itself dispatch a sub-task, creating a Directed Acyclic Graph of suspended contexts. The inference engine will manage a stack of KV caches.

Distributed Dispatchers: Sharding frozen KV caches across a cluster of inference nodes, allowing a sub-agent suspended on Node A to be resumed on Node B (requires standardized KV cache serialization formats).
